						               													<description>The tensions have boiled over at this televised baking competition after the trash talk went too far. Now it's time to put down the whisk and put up your dukes. No one insults your cinnamon rolls. No one!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2-4 players each grab their favorite set of seven standard role-playing dice (d4, d6, d8, d10, d10%, d12, d20) and start by rolling all of them. Those seven dice are their bakery crew, from which they will secretly pick one chef to throw a cinnamon roll (Roll) or throw a punch (Fight) each round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Everybody reveals their choices, then the players who chose Roll get to pick one chef to be rerolled. But beware; chefs on Fight can get a bonus reroll if picked! The highest result wins and claims all of the round's chefs as points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;However, if everyone chose to Roll, each chef is rerolled once instead. Or if everyone chose to Fight, then the bravest and lowest result wins outright. After seven rounds of flying fists and pastries the bakery with the most points wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
